appen? Can you be disciplined on marketing and just with product intervention, grow the user base by a substantial number?\n\n**Mr Vijay Shekhar Sharma:** Absolutely. And in fact, I want to tell you that the growth in user base did happen without, in fact, we cut the marketing in these quarters to show only and give the confidence to the team that your product matters. So as you are seeing the numbers, that is because of the good product and better product attention.\n\nAnd I want to give you another surprise, Manish. It is lesser number of people, more attention to the product that has got this. So lower cost in people operating, lower cost in marketing, resulting in growth.\n\nAnd I do believe without gangbuster marketing expenditure, we would be able to get it back. I do believe and I'm seeing it also."], "questions": ["Given the stated focus on merchant growth and the current consumer base for future revenue and profit, what specific product-led initiatives are being prioritized to attract and retain the targeted 200-250 million highly repeat users, and what is the projected timeline for achieving this user base?", "How does the company plan to balance the 'disciplined marketing' approach with the objective of substantial user base growth, particularly in light of the past reliance on marketing expenditure to drive user acquisition?", "Beyond product improvements and feature adoption like the 'hide payment' option, what are the key drivers and metrics that will indicate a sustainable recovery and growth in the consumer user base, and how will these be measured against the goal of 200-250 million repeat users?"], "doc_name": "paytm2", "url": "https://s3-qa-8byte.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/paytm%2Fin%2Fpaytm2.pdf", "page_number": 5, "tenant_id": "1c04c95e-867f-4956-99b3-7f86c0565789", "file_id": "7b5a7749-129d-4d86-9070-d90a979b1f2b", "tenant_name": "Paytm", "entities": ["NPCI", "MTUs", "EBITDA", "UPI", "GMV"]}, {"sddocname": "pefund", "documentid": "id:pefund:pe